  "text": "Microservices versus monolithic. Quick comparison. Monolith ship fast, one code base, one deploy, simple ops. The downside, scaling means scaling everything, even parts that don't need it. Microservices scale independently. Different teams, different stacks, different release cadences. The cost, network latency, distributed tracing and operational overhead that grows with every service. Most teams should start with a monolith. Split when the seams hurt.",
